INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (86, 1, '2014-07-14 11:07:00', '2014-07-14 11:07:00', 'Maybe it was the jetlag, taking over a whole day to get from the states to Kenya, or the sheer excitement of this trip being my first with Charlene; but sleeping was the last thing on my mind when we arrived at the Safari Park Hotel in Nairobi. Seemed like the minutes were moving like hours, and the hours like days, but eventually, the sun came up around 6AM and we made our way to the dining hall for breakfast. Little did we realize that standing next to us in the buffet line and sitting a few tables across would be our new traveler friends (more on them later!). <a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_01_04.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-80" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_01_04.jpg" alt="01_01_04" width="960" height="640" /></a>\r\n\r\nAfter eating our first meal of the trip, Charlene and I decided to take a stroll around the hotel while we waited for our safari tour to officially start. It felt like we had the whole place to ourselves, with not a single soul in sight. On a random note, we saw a merry-go-round and even a sign that pointed to a casino. Being that photography and travel played a huge part in Charlene and I getting to meet and know one another, it was only fitting to take a few self-portraits, including the classic jumping in the air shot.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_01_01.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-82" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_01_01.jpg" alt="01_01_01" width="960" height="640" /></a> As the sun slowly started to rise above the horizon, we eventually made our way to the lobby and met up with our tour group. Not only was this the first time Charlene and I were traveling together, but it was also my first time going in a group (with new strangers). It didn’t occur to me that we would all literally be together for the next 7+ days of the safari tour. Everything was truly a brand new experience for me. But looking back after the trip, meeting our new friends was one of the highlights. We all said our “Hellos”, grabbed our suitcases, and made our way to the somewhat beat-up but still good as new safari van. Our adventure was just beginning.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_01_03.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-84" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_01_03.jpg" alt="01_01_03" width="960" height="640" /></a>', 'Morning Walk Around Safari Park Hotel', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '67-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-14 11:07:00', '2014-07-14 11:07:00', '', 67, 'http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//67-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
