INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (103, 1, '2014-07-14 11:24:14', '2014-07-14 11:24:14', 'After a few hours of driving through the bustling city of Nairobi and passing by the Great Rift Valley, we were now about an hour away from our Masai Mara lodge, where not only an afternoon game drive awaited us, but freshly squeezed orange juice, a wet towel to help freshen up, and a hot lunch!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_03_05.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-98" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_03_05.jpg" alt="01_03_05" width="960" height="640" /></a><a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_03_03.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-100" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_03_03.jpg" alt="01_03_03" width="960" height="640" /></a>\r\n\r\nAs the road beneath our safari van slowly turned from concrete to dirt, and cows, sheeps, and even a few giraffes replaced automobiles and stores, we realized that we were that much closer to our destination for the next few days. But in the near distance, we noticed another safari van parked on what appeared like the side of the dirt road and several travelers were on standby.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-102" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_03_01.jpg" alt="01_03_01" width="960" height="640" />\r\n\r\nAs we got closer to the stationed van, our driver Hodge let us know that a small bridge we were supposed to drive over had turned had turned into a huge ditch, and thus we would need to go around it. The other van had attempted to do just that but ended up being stuck in the dirt. Being the gentleman that Hodge was, he parked our van right in front of the other and helped tow it out of the rut!\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-101" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_03_04.jpg" alt="01_03_04" width="960" height="640" />\r\n\r\nI’m sure eventually another van would’ve driven by and helped out the one stuck in the dirt, or perhaps the nearest AAA of Kenya would’ve came by (not sure how long that would’ve taken!), but it brought a warm, fuzzy feeling to all our hearts to see Hodge lend a helping hand, or rather a helping tow! After many applauses and elation by the other van’s driver and travelers, we were finally on our way to the lodge!\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-99" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_03_02.jpg" alt="01_03_02" width="960" height="640" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Lending A Helping Tow', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '97-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-14 11:24:14', '2014-07-14 11:24:14', '', 97, 'http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//97-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (104, 1, '2014-07-14 11:33:41', '2014-07-14 11:33:41', 'After a 24+ hours of flying and finally landing in Nairobi around 10PM, we were not only ready to stretch our legs but also get a warm shower and good night sleep before starting the safari tour the next morning. As soon as we got to the arrival gate with our luggages, two young gentlemen holding our names greeted us with warm smiles and introduced themselves as drivers from Safari Park Hotel, the place where we would be spending the evening.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_02.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-113" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_02.jpg" alt="01_04_02" width="960" height="640" /></a>\r\n\r\nI remember the drive from the airport to the lodge being no more than around 20-25 minutes, and it went by that much faster since we were having a great time chatting it up with the two drivers. Upon arrival at Safari Park Hotel, we were shown to our room where we finally had the chance to relax and prepare for the upcoming adventure. Although we were still in the city, the entire lodge felt like we were already one with nature, with dozens of trees and greenery surrounding us.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_01.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-112" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_01.jpg" alt="01_04_01" width="960" height="640" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEven Though we arrived pretty late (close to 11PM), we felt very safe walking around the lodge. And if I recall, although the lodge provided nets around the bed, mosquitoes and other bugs weren’t that big of an issue. The only thing I wished Safari Park Hotel had was some sort of late night meal service, as I was pretty hungry after a long day of flying. The good news was breakfast started extra early (around 5AM).\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_04.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-110" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_04.jpg" alt="01_04_04" width="960" height="640" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn the morning, not only were we able to get the first meal of the day even before the sun came up, but it was a buffet with delicious Western-style choices from eggs and bacon to fresh coffee and juice. We even had some time after breakfast to take a quick stroll around the lodge before packing our bags and meeting our safari tour group. All the staff members were courteous and helpful. I especially remembered the tall gentleman at the front door of the lobby who greeted us with a warm smile.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_10.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-105" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_10.jpg" alt="01_04_10" width="960" height="640" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_07.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-109" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_07.jpg" alt="01_04_07" width="960" height="640" /></a> <a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_06.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-108" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_06.jpg" alt="01_04_06" width="960" height="640" /></a> <a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_08.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-106" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_08.jpg" alt="01_04_08" width="960" height="640" /></a> <a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_03.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-114" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_03.jpg" alt="01_04_03" width="960" height="640" /></a> <a href="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_05.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-111" src="http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//wp-content/uploads/2014/07/01_04_05.jpg" alt="01_04_05" width="960" height="640" /></a>\r\n\r\nMeals: <strong>Breakfast (included)</strong>\r\n\r\nWarm shower: <strong>Yes</strong>\r\n\r\nWIFI: <strong>No</strong>\r\n\r\nRecommend: <strong>Yes</strong>', 'Safari Park Hotel', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'safari-park-hotel', '', '', '2014-07-17 07:12:16', '2014-07-17 07:12:16', '', 0, 'http://clients.plusplusminus.co.za/oada//?p=104', 0, 'post', '', 0) ; 
